* AMENDED *

- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, L. Abdullah her residence and place of employment.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats. If the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bail jumping.

CO: Vlack, Reporter: Gross, Clerk: Liddle. ADA:  Bela Alexander Ballo   DF ATTY:  Abrianna Dolfi   DF:  Najee Bilal Abdullah appeared from jail. Erin M from Victim Witness is present. Case called at 4:42 p.m. Court notes this matter is set for a status. Jury trial is scheduled for tomorrow. ADA Ballo is moving for a continuance. Gives argument. Witness is being uncooperative. State is not interested at dismissing at this time. Exploring a forfeiture by wrong doing. Atty Dolfi states DE made a speedy trial demand and objects to continuance request. Response by ADA Ballo. Court will grant continuance and amend bond. Court adjourned at 4:53 p.m.  Status conference scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
